http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Tiruchirapalli/Wi-Fi-facility-now-available-at-Tiruchi-airport/article13978010.ece

Tiruchi joined the other international airports in the country in providing modern communication facilities to travellers with the launch of the Wi-Fi internet service at the airport.The Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limited (BSNL) has installed the Wi-Fi network free of cost to the Airports Authority of India (AAI) as part of an understanding between them.The AAI has provided the space with the BSNL providing the facility for the benefit of domestic and international travellers arriving and departing from the airport.The BSNL has partnered with the Quadgen Wireless Solution for providing the facility which was inaugurated by Tiruchi Member of Parliament P. Kumar on Friday in the presence of the Airport Director B.C.H. Negi, and BSNL Principal General Manager Raju.The Wi-Fi coverage has been provided both at the departure and arrival lounges at the airport from where foreign airlines operate services to Colombo, Kuala Lumpur, Singapore, and Dubai every day.Domestic and international passengers can use the Wi-Fi free for the first 15 minutes once a month.Those wanting Wi-Fi access after the free usage could get it for 30 minutes (Rs. 30), 60 (Rs. 50), or 90 minutes (Rs. 90) or one day (Rs. 150) by making on-line payment.